Description: CVE-2026-40164 - Replace hardcoded MurmurHash3 seed with randomized seed
 jq used MurmurHash3 with a publicly visible hardcoded seed (0x432A9843) for
 all JSON object hash table operations, allowing attackers to precompute key
 collisions offline. A crafted JSON object forces all keys into the same hash
 bucket, degrading lookup from O(1) to O(n) and causing O(n^2) CPU exhaustion.
 This patch initializes the seed from a random source at process startup.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/jqlang/jq/commit/0c7d133c3c7e37c00b6d46b658a02244fdd3c784
Author: itchyny <itchyny@cybozu.co.jp>
Last-Update: 2026-04-15

--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -130,11 +130,16 @@
