Description: CVE-2026-39979 - Fix out-of-bounds read in jv_parse_sized()
 Fix out-of-bounds read in jv_parse_sized() error path by using %.*s
 with explicit length instead of %s. When malformed JSON is passed in a
 non-NUL-terminated buffer, the error construction logic performs an
 out-of-bounds read past the end of the buffer.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/jqlang/jq/commit/2f09060afab23fe9390cce7cb860b10416e1bf5f
Author: itchyny <itchyny@cybozu.co.jp>
Last-Update: 2026-04-15

--- a/src/jv_parse.c
+++ b/src/jv_parse.c
@@ -845,8 +845,9 @@ jv jv_parse_sized(const char* string, int length) {

   if (!jv_is_valid(value) && jv_invalid_has_msg(jv_copy(value))) {
     jv msg = jv_invalid_get_msg(value);
-    value = jv_invalid_with_msg(jv_string_fmt("%s (while parsing '%s')",
+    value = jv_invalid_with_msg(jv_string_fmt("%s (while parsing '%.*s')",
                                               jv_string_value(msg),
+                                              length,
                                               string));
     jv_free(msg);
   }
Description: CVE-2026-49839 - Fix heap-buffer-overflow in raw file loading
